      "writtenOn": "2016-07-13T14:55:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m worried about crash keys that are set repeatedly with different values. The interned string table is going to collect a lot of garbage. Perhaps Grow() is a feature of the ContiguousStringMap instead. That way it can erase old string data as it doubles its capacity.",
